Dear Pee Pee:<br><br>
Served from Jan 17, 1961 to Apr 15, 1975.  Was enlisted man for five years, warrant officer for a year and a couple months..received a direct commission in RVN Feb 15, 1967.<br>
First tour..III Corps.. First Combat Aviation Brigade, 12th Combat Aviation Group, 145th Combat Aviation Battalion, 68th Assault Helicopter Company (Top Tigers).  Flew slicks for a while.. went to the Guns (Mustangs).. went TDY to the US Navy Operation Seawolf.. flew cover in the Rung Sat Special Swamp Zone.. supported Seal Team for 90 days.  Assigned to Special Forces team for prepatory work for operation Junction City.<br>
Second Tour...III Corps...(Jan 69)flew Cobras all over.. mostly night... Test pilot.. broke back in August..medivaced to Japan in September...medivaced to Ft. Gordon in November.<br>
Paralyzed for three months. (Okay Now!) Wounded five times on first tour.<br>
Recognized in the Proceedings and Debates of the 101st Congress of the United States, Second Session, in Washington on Wednesday, June 27, 1990. Presented 42 additional decorations over 24 already previously awarded.  See Vol. 136 page 84.<br>
Graduated from the University of Tulsa.  Post graduate work done at Oklahoma State University.<br>
First runner up for Native American of the Year 1996.<br>
Presently, free lance writer and principle idol for Cook Barela...bale hay and build garages.<br>
Do a lot of free counsel and other help for local homeless veterans etc.<br>
Fly helicopters for Native American Firefighters on occassions...last time was for the Navaho nation.<br>
That's about it...except for the secret stuff (would have to kill everybody if I told you!)<br>
If you need specifics... email me.<br><br>
Thanks for the honor of asking...sort'a validates a fellow!<br><br>
